The Lagos State Commissioner of Police, Hakeem Odumosu, has tightened security around JKK House on Ikorodu Road, Ilupeju, Lagos, venue of the computer-based test for the Nigeria Police Regular Course 8 intakes. The state Police Public Relations Officer, Muyiwa Ogunjobi, said Odumosu also assessed the venue on Thursday. He noted that the CP urged all the applicants and those involved in the exercise to observe the COVID-19 protocols and follow the examination rules and regulations. “Before the commencement of the examination, the CP had deployed adequate police personnel for the protection of lives and property of the applicants and examiners at the centre, considering the large number of applicants from within and outside Lagos State. “The police chief was accompanied by a delegate of examiners from the Police Academy, Wudil, Kano, including the Assistant Commissioner of Police, Legal Studies, ACP AbdulSalam Alade; the lecturer at the Police Academy, Dr Boumo Ezombi; the Area Commander, Area F, Ikeja, ACP John Zongo; and some operational officers in the area. “CP Odumosu reaffirmed the readiness of the Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, to have a world class and standardised police institution in Nigeria through reorganised recruitment exercises,” Adejobi added. Copyright PUNCH.
